  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to the health effects of drought in Lesotho</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide drought-linked disease outbreak control and response services and emergency maternal and child health interventions to those suffering direct consequence of drought in eight districts of Lesotho. WHO will use CERF funds to respond to outbreaks associated with the prevailing drought (diarrhoeal disease, anthrax outbreaks and measles), support management of severe acute malnutrition and other childhood illnesses in hospitals, distribute disposable delivery kits, and provide targeted WASH assistance to health facilities. An estimated 24,000 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented in six months.</narrative>
  </description>
